External knowledge: 
 Completed projects and sprints refer to those with a non-null end date in their respective tables; 
 Story points are a unit of measure for expressing an estimate of the overall effort required to fully implement a product backlog item or any other piece of work;
 Velocity, in the context of agile project management, is a measure of the amount of work a team can complete during a sprint.
